HEADWORD: Concupiscent
<hw>Con*cu"pis*cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>concupiscens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>concupiscere</ets>, v. incho. of
<ets>concupere</ets> to long for; <ets>con-</ets> + <ets>cupere</ets>.
See <er>Covet</er>.]</ety> <def>Having sexual lust; libidinous; lustful;
lecherous; salacious.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

